<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 8:29PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern Gilmer,
southern Murray, south central Whitfield, Gordon and northwestern
Pickens Counties through 900 PM EDT...
At 829 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Sugar Valley to Audubon to near Tails Creek, and
moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Ellijay, East Ellijay, Resaca, Talking Rock, Fairmount,
Ranger, Carters, Sonoraville, Talona, Tails Creek, Ramhurst,
Oostanaula, Redbud, Tilton, Audubon, Cartecay, Blaine, Sugar Valley
and Oakman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
